Lower value of 'F' results in higher probability of node to be considered failed early even if that node is not dead.

Test case 4 (set c = 10)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

N  b c  F  B P S T
10 4 10 10 4 5 1 30

  9        8        7        6       5        4         3       2        1        0

 OK    |  FAIL  |  FAIL  |  OK    |  OK    |  OK    |  FAIL  |  OK    |  FAIL  |  OK
 0 9   |  0 14  |  0 9   |  0 9   |  0 9   |  0 9   |  0 5   |  0 8   |  0 18  |  1 8
 1 9   |  1 14  |  1 9   |  1 9   |  1 19  |  1 9   |  1 5   |  1 8   |  2 9   |  2 8
 2 9   |  2 9   |  2 9   |  2 29  |  2 29  |  2 29  |  2 5   |  3 5   |  3 5   |  3 5
 3 5   |  3 5   |  3 5   |  3 5   |  3 5   |  3 5   |  4 5   |  4 8   |  4 19  |  4 9
 4 9   |  4 14  |  4 9   |  4 29  |  4 29  |  5 29  |  5 5   |  5 8   |  5 9   |  5 29
 5 29  |  5 9   |  5 9   |  5 29  |  6 29  |  6 8   |  6 4   |  6 7   |  6 9   |  6 29
 6 9   |  6 8   |  6 9   |  7 9   |  7 9   |  7 9   |  7 5   |  7 8   |  7 9   |  7 9
